      • isObjectMethod

        public static boolean isObjectMethod(ExecutableElement method)
        Checks whether the specified method is one of the methods declared by the Object class. Hence, the method returns true if the specified method is one of
        • Object.clone()
        • Object.finalize()
        • Object.getClass()
        • Object.hashCode()
        • Object.notify()
        • Object.notifyAll()
        • Object.toString()
        • Object.wait()
        • Object.equals(Object)
        • Object.wait(long)
        • Object.wait(long, int)
        Parameters:
        method - the method to check
        Returns:
        true if this method was declared by Object, false otherwise.

      • getInfosFromParamList

        public static List<ParameterInfo> getInfosFromParamList(List<? extends VariableElement> veList,
                                        boolean varArgs)
                                                 throws IllegalArgumentException
        Turns a list of VariableElements into a ParameterInfo list.
        Parameters:
        veList - the list of VariableElements
        varArgs - whether this parameter list is of a varargs method. If set to true, the last parameter must have an array type and is interpreted as a varargs parameter
        Returns:
        the corresponding list of ParameterInfo objects
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if one of the following conditions is true:
        • one of the elements of veList is null
        • one of the elements of veList has a null type or name
        • varArgs is set to true, but veList is empty
        • varArgs is set to true, but the type of the last element of veList is not an array type

      • getParameterInfos

        public static List<ParameterInfo> getParameterInfos(ExecutableElement method)
        Turns the parameter list of an ExecutableElement into a list of ParameterInfo objects.

        This is a convenience method, equivalent to 

         fromParamList(method.getParameters(), method.isVarArgs())
        Parameters:
        method - the method from which to retrieve the parameter list
        Returns:
        the corresponding list of ParameterInfo objects
